Omolara Akintoye The Association of Nigerian Women Business Network (ANWBN) on Monday condemned the gruesome murder of the People’s Deputy Party (PDP) woman leader, Acheju Salome Abuh, who was burnt alive during the just concluded November 16th Governorship election in Kogi State. The National Coordinator, Chief Mrs. Anita Nana Okuribido , the National Executive, Members of the Coalition comprising of over three million members across the country are horrified and demand for justice. “We don’t understand why someone’s life should be eliminated to gain political ground or gain. This is painful and totally unacceptable. The perpetrators of this crime against humanity, womanhood and fair play must be brought to book. We therefore call for urgent legal action,” said Okuribido. ANWBN also console her immediate family at this time.